Obviously being non binary isn't all about gender presentation and clothes but I feel like it's the easiest example to talk about because I can't describe my internal feelings about it lol

I feel like I enjoy femme things that are over top like Lolita fashion or my strawberry tracksuit combo but buying "professional" clothes for my old job was extremely stressful. I know there are lots of cis women who are like "I just like wearing jeans and a t-shirt"

I also feel like if I say "I hated wearing make up to look professional" I know a lot of cis women feel the same way so I don't know why it's different for me. 

Normie make up for work - makes me feel terrible

Bright pink eyeshadow for Lolita fashion - makes me feel amazing

So I'd be like "yea people can wear whatever they want" but then have all these secret rules for myself. 

I don't know if this is relatable to anyone or not

I try to write tweets about gender related stuff and then I read them back and they barely make sense to me so they won't make sense to anyone else. 

But like basically I had all of these weird made up rules in my head that I didn't think applied to other people only me

I'm Autistic and ADHD and my husband has ADHD and looking after a full section was not doable at all and we couldn't afford to pay for a gardener. We are currently building a new house and we're getting a lot of the yard concreted so we don't have to do as much.

I'm not saying that you shouldn't be informed, educate or advocate for yourself but sometimes the best thing you can do for your physical or mental health is know that if there's some huge breakthrough you'll hear about it but in the meantime you can also just exist.
